         <notesStmt>
            <note type="summary">Z. is happy about the news that R. Moses Capsuto and R.
                            Moses Franko will join him and Benjamin ha-Kohen on their journey to the
                            Holy Land. He then discusses logistical questions of the trip. Exhorts
                            Kohen to recruit more sponsors to finance the journey like R. Joseph
                            Hayyim. He asks Kohen to write to Capsuto that he is happy about Franko
                            joining, and asks him to extend the sponsorship to their yeshiva. Z.
                            offers to write to Frank himself, if Capsuto thinks this would be
                            beneficial.</note>
            <note type="incipit" xml:lang="he">כמה וכמה טובה כפולה
                        גמלתני</note>
